OL,3,CGuernsey's Merrien takes 5th world
OL,4,Ctitle down under
OL,6,FGuernsey's Alison Merrien MBE has been
OL,7,Fcrowned world champion for a fifth
OL,8,Ftime after winning the World Indoor
OL,9,FBowls Championship.
OL,11,FThe Sarnian bowler won the women's
OL,12,Fsingles title in Victoria, Australia,
OL,13,Fbeating Scotland's Julie Forrest in
OL,14,Fstraight sets.
OL,16,FThis is her first Women's singles
OL,17,Fworld title since 2019. Her success on
OL,18,Fthe world stage now spans nealry two
OL,19,Fdecades after victory in 2018, 2015
OL,20,Fand 2009.
